pointer->const

beej, ch.16

(1) cannot change val to which pointer points, but pointer itself
    - const <type> *p (equivalent to: <type> const *p)
(2) cannot change pointer, but pointed-to val
    - <type> *const p
(3) cannot modify val nor pointer
    - const <type> *const p

EXAMPLE
(1)
int x[] = {10, 20};
const int *p1 = x;
printf("%d\n", *p1); // 10
p1++;
printf("%d\n", *p1); // 20
(2)
int *const p2 = x;
*p2 = 20;
for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) printf("%d ", x[i]); // 20 20
